status: MARC21-007: Base of film of microform

definition (en): Acetate safety base film whose exact type cannot be determined.
Combination of nitrate base and safety base film.
A reflective rather than a transparent base.
scope note (en): Used for microopaques (which can be termed microcard or microprint).

definition (en): Film base is made of a synthetic resin (e.g., estar).
Mixed safety base films are spliced together; no nitrate film.

Base of film other than safety base, undetermined, safety base, acetate undetermined, safety base, diacetate, nitrate base, mixed base (nitrate and safety), not applicable, safety base, polyester, safety base, mixed, safety base, triacetate.
